CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 22, 1954, pg. 27, reads: "Uptown Little League Opener - A throng of some five hundred baseball fans saw the North Side Elks down the Pittsburgh Lions by a 1-0 score at Kennard Field, last Saturday, as Jack Bishop's homer decided the issue... Lower right: Umpires who worked the game, left to right, are J. McCollum, Dave Meff, J. Gilliam, Boots Turner and Charles Betts. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Little League baseball umpires J. McCollum, Dave Meff, J. Gilliam, Boots Turner, and Charles Betts on Kennard Field during Uptown Little League opening day
